fields.name: Simone
fields.description:
An ideal choice for every chocolate lover. Simone delights with the aroma of toasted hazelnuts and organic cocoa. This  cake is characterized by an elegant taste of cocoa cream sweetened with agave syrup and a base sweetened with dates, without added sugar.  Chopped hazelnuts give it an indispensable finishing touch.





INGREDIENTS: Cashews, hazelnuts, agave syrup, water, coconut oil, cocoa, dates, maple syrup.

fields.name: Aurelie
fields.description:
Aurelie is a healthy version of the world classic - the already well-known carrot cake. Organic almond and spelt flour with carrots from Irish family farms, together form a soft and juicy biscuit. The whole story is perfectly complemented by a refreshing cream of cream cheese, orange and erythritol - a calorie-free sugar. For true enjoyment without guilt.

INGREDIENTS: Almond milk, almond flour, spelt flour, eggs, brown sugar, carrots, butter, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, cream cheese, erythritol, orange.

fields.name: Rosalie
fields.description:
Step into the berry paradise with our vegan beauty - Rosalie. Allow yourself to be overwhelmed by the freshness and light acidity of the forest fruits in combination with the sweet base of organically grown cashews and almonds. Topped with berry glaze to give the final decedent note to the cake.

INGREDIENTS: Cashews, almonds, coconut, dates, cinnamon, agave syrup, lemon, forest fruits (raspberry, blueberry, blackberry, red currant, black currant).

fields.name: Nicolette
fields.description:
An exotic combination of flavors that leaves no one indifferent. Our Nicolette has a perfect ratio of sweet and spicy. The pleasure ranges from the very base of organic cashews, almonds and coconuts sweetened with dates, to a smooth cream of vanilla and lime sweetened with maple syrup. The addition of cinnamon gives it an extra touch of class. 

INGREDIENTS: almonds, cashews, dates, cinnamon, coconut, maple syrup, lime.

fields.name: Sourdough Bread
fields.description:
In a nutshell, sourdough is slow-fermented bread.
It’s unique because it does not require commercial yeast in order to rise.
Instead, it’s made with a live fermented culture, a sourdough starter, which acts as a natural leavening agent. Sourdough is known for its characteristic tangy flavor, chewy texture and crisp, crackly crust.

From a health standpoint, it dominates when compared to supermarket loaves. The naturally occurring acids and long fermentation help to break down the gluten, making it more digestible and easy for the body to absorb. 

And it tastes darn good!

fields.name: Overnight Rye Bread
fields.description: Our overnight rye bread is an easier version of a northern European classic, made with whole grain spelt and rye flour, and oats. This dense bread is not at all dry and makes a nice alternative to light loaves, with a stronger flavour and slightly chewy texture.

fields.name: Foccacia
fields.description:
Our Foccacia is perfectly soft and fluffy and satisfyingly chewy. It’s sprinkled with lots of fresh rosemary and crunchy flaky sea salt. When drizzled with extra olive oil just before serving, it soaks perfectly into all of those little classic holes in the bread. 

It also happens to be naturally vegan.

And best of all, it is just the ultimate cozy carbohydrate comfort food. 

I know you’re going to love it.

fields.name: Brioche Bread
fields.description:
This originally French bread made with butter and eggs, is extremely light in texture and has a subtle sweetness in its flavor. Brioche crust is soft, with a golden-yellow shade. This gorgeous golden color can be attributed to the egg that is brushed on top of the dough before the bread is placed in an oven to bake. Brioche bread is a perfect bread choice, especially when making delicious treats like French toast.
 
If you’ve never tasted this type of bread before, there is no better time than right now to grab a loaf of soft, slightly sweet brioche.
